hwCluster.name: hwCluster
hwCluster.contactinfo: Platform Team Huawei 3Com Technologies Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.huawei-3com.com Zip:100085
hwCluster.description: This MIB contains objects to manage the hgmp operations, which are used on lanswitch products.

hwClusterObject.name: hwClusterObject
hwClusterObject.description: This MIB contains objects to manage the cluster operations, which are used on lanswitch products.

hgmpSetVLANSecurity.name: hgmpSetVLANSecurity
hgmpSetVLANSecurity.description: Configure whether to perform the VLAN check inside the cluster.

hgmpHandShakeInterval.name: hgmpHandShakeInterval
hgmpHandShakeInterval.description: Handshaking interval of the cluster member switches.

hgmpHandShakeHoldtime.name: hgmpHandShakeHoldtime
hgmpHandShakeHoldtime.description: Holdtime of administrator switch and member switch in the cluster.

hgmpGrpMemberTableChange.name: hgmpGrpMemberTableChange
hgmpGrpMemberTableChange.description: Add 1 to the member list after it changes. The administrator checks if the value has changed. If not, he will not read the list once more.

hgmpMemberDisconRate.name: hgmpMemberDisconRate
hgmpMemberDisconRate.description: Disconnection times of the member and administrator switches divided by member number times 1000.

hgmpCmdClusterName.name: hgmpCmdClusterName
hgmpCmdClusterName.description: Cluster name of the administrator switch

hgmpMngPriIpSegCMIP.name: hgmpMngPriIpSegCMIP
hgmpMngPriIpSegCMIP.description: The private management IP address of the administrator switch, which can not be modified after the cluster has been created.

hgmpMngPriIpMask.name: hgmpMngPriIpMask
hgmpMngPriIpMask.description: The private management IP address mask assigned by the administrator switch, which cannot be modified after the cluster has been created.

hgmpFtpServer.name: hgmpFtpServer
hgmpFtpServer.description: The cluster members can access the Ftp Server through the administrator switch, which can only be configured and accessed on the administrator switch.

hgmpTftpServer.name: hgmpTftpServer
hgmpTftpServer.description: The cluster members can access the Tftp Server through the administrator switch, which can only be configured and accessed on the administrator switch.

hgmpSnmpHost.name: hgmpSnmpHost
hgmpSnmpHost.description: The Snmp Host to send the cluster trap packets, which can only be configured and accessed on the administrator switch.

hgmpLogHost.name: hgmpLogHost
hgmpLogHost.description: Log host of the cluster, which can only be configured and accessed on the administrator switch.

hgmpGrpMemberDeviceId.name: hgmpGrpMemberDeviceId
hgmpGrpMemberDeviceId.description: 4 bytes reserved as 0x0 + 6 bytes of MAC address, expressed as a character string of the hexadecimal number.

hgmpGrpMemberSerial.name: hgmpGrpMemberSerial
hgmpGrpMemberSerial.description: When adding member switch to the cluster, the administrator switch will assign an unique integer to identify it.

hgmpGrpMemberIpAddr.name: hgmpGrpMemberIpAddr
hgmpGrpMemberIpAddr.description: The private IP addresses of the member switches for the communication inside the cluster.

hgmpGrpMemberPassword.name: hgmpGrpMemberPassword
hgmpGrpMemberPassword.description: Member password for joining a cluster

hgmpGrpMemberPlatform.name: hgmpGrpMemberPlatform
hgmpGrpMemberPlatform.description: Set the hardware platform. A null string indicates the information does not exist in the device adjacency table.

hgmpGrpMemberStatus.name: hgmpGrpMemberStatus
hgmpGrpMemberStatus.description: Member status on the administrator switch, use for displaying the network management status.

hgmpGrpMemberDisconCount.name: hgmpGrpMemberDisconCount
hgmpGrpMemberDisconCount.description: Count of inside communication disconnection between the member switch and the administrator switch.

hgmpGrpMemberEnrollTime.name: hgmpGrpMemberEnrollTime
hgmpGrpMemberEnrollTime.description: Enrollment time of the member, measured in seconds.

hgmpGrpMemberOperate.name: hgmpGrpMemberOperate
hgmpGrpMemberOperate.description: Operation indication field, indicates the operation of adding/removing a member by the network management agent.

hgmpMemberResetTable.name: hgmpMemberResetTable
hgmpMemberResetTable.description: Reset a member switch in the cluster.

hgmpMemberResetMAC.name: hgmpMemberResetMAC
hgmpMemberResetMAC.description: The management MAC address of the switch to be reset, which is the unique identifier of the switch.

hgmpMemberEraseflash.name: hgmpMemberEraseflash
hgmpMemberEraseflash.description: Whether to erase the configuration file from the flash after resetting the switch. Read this node, cannotget(65535) will be returned.

hgmpMemberfailure.name: hgmpMemberfailure
hgmpMemberfailure.description: When a cluster member failure, send a snmp trap to the network management.

hgmpMemberRecover.name: hgmpMemberRecover
hgmpMemberRecover.description: When a cluster member recover, send a snmp trap to the network management.

hgmpMemberStatusChange.name: hgmpMemberStatusChange
hgmpMemberStatusChange.description: When a cluster member status change, send a snmp trap to the network management.

hgmpNetTopChange.name: hgmpNetTopChange
hgmpNetTopChange.description: When net topology of this cluster change, send a snmp trap to the network management.

hgmpClusterMaxPoolNum.name: hgmpClusterMaxPoolNum
hgmpClusterMaxPoolNum.description: Max switch members that the cluster can support(include administrator switch).

hgmpClusterCmdSwMac.name: hgmpClusterCmdSwMac
hgmpClusterCmdSwMac.description: The MAC address of administrator switch. It will be filled with zero when not be a member of cluster.

hgmpClusterProtocolMac.name: hgmpClusterProtocolMac
hgmpClusterProtocolMac.description: Protocol MAC of HGMP protocol family. All multicast packets of this protocol family use this MAC as destination MAC.

hgmpWhitelistTable.name: hgmpWhitelistTable
hgmpWhitelistTable.description: Cluster switches white list table. White list topology is the topology which has been affirmed by network administrator in a cluster, and all devices in white list topology are recorded in this table. Against to white list table, black list table records the devices which are denied to join in cluster. Adding a black list device to white list table will cause a failure.

hgmpWhitelistDeviceId.name: hgmpWhitelistDeviceId
hgmpWhitelistDeviceId.description: Unique identifier indicating a white list switch. Value format of the this object is 'XXXXYYYYYY', in which 'XXXX' is reserved as 4 bytes of 0x0, 'YYYYYY' is a MAC address. For example, if the MAC is 000f-e459-000a, the value of this object is an octet string: '00' '00' '00' '00' '00' '0f' 'e4' '59' '00' '0a'.

hgmpWhitelistSerial.name: hgmpWhitelistSerial
hgmpWhitelistSerial.description: When adding member switch to the cluster, the administrator switch will assign an unique integer to identify it. 0xffff means invalid value for this object.

hgmpWhitelistRowStatus.name: hgmpWhitelistRowStatus
hgmpWhitelistRowStatus.description: The row status of this table.

hgmpWhitelistNbTable.name: hgmpWhitelistNbTable
hgmpWhitelistNbTable.description: Cluster switches white list neighboring information table. White list neighbor table records all neighbor devices for every white list device. In fact, white list neighbor table displays the whole white list topology.

hgmpWhitelistNbIndex.name: hgmpWhitelistNbIndex
hgmpWhitelistNbIndex.description: Index of a switch which is the neighbor of a white list switch identified by 'hgmpWhitelistDeviceId'.

hgmpWhitelistNbDeviceId.name: hgmpWhitelistNbDeviceId
hgmpWhitelistNbDeviceId.description: Unique identifier indicating a neighbor switch of a white list switch. Value format of the this object is 'XXXXYYYYYY', in which 'XXXX' is reserved as 4 bytes of 0x0, 'YYYYYY' is a MAC address. For example, if the MAC is 000f-e459-000a, the value of this object is an octet string: '00' '00' '00' '00' '00' '0f' 'e4' '59' '00' '0a'.

hgmpWhitelistPortName.name: hgmpWhitelistPortName
hgmpWhitelistPortName.description: The name of the port which a white list switch connects to the neighbor specified by 'hgmpWhitelistNbIndex'.

hgmpWhitelistNbPortName.name: hgmpWhitelistNbPortName
hgmpWhitelistNbPortName.description: The name of the port which a neighbor device connects to the white list switch specified by 'hgmpWhitelistDeviceId'.

hgmpBlacklistTable.name: hgmpBlacklistTable
hgmpBlacklistTable.description: Cluster switches black list table. The black list table records all black list devices, and a device in black list is not permitted to join in any cluster.

hgmpBlacklistDeviceId.name: hgmpBlacklistDeviceId
hgmpBlacklistDeviceId.description: Unique identifier indicating a black list switch. Value format of the this object is 'XXXXYYYYYY', in which 'XXXX' is reserved as 4 bytes of 0x0, 'YYYYYY' is a MAC address. For example, if the MAC is 000f-e459-000a, the value of this object is an octet string: '00' '00' '00' '00' '00' '0f' 'e4' '59' '00' '0a'.

hgmpBlacklistAccessDeviceId.name: hgmpBlacklistAccessDeviceId
hgmpBlacklistAccessDeviceId.description: Unique identifier indicating the access device of a black list switch. Tracing from a black list device to the cluster commander switch, the device which the black list switch directly connects to is the access device. Value format of the this object is 'XXXXYYYYYY', in which 'XXXX' is reserved as 4 bytes of 0x0, 'YYYYYY' is a MAC address. 10 bytes of 0xff means invalid value for this object. For example, if the MAC is 000f-e459-000a, the value of this object is an octet string: '00' '00' '00' '00' '00' '0f' 'e4' '59' '00' '0a'.

hgmpBlacklistAccessPortName.name: hgmpBlacklistAccessPortName
hgmpBlacklistAccessPortName.description: The port which the access device connecting to the black list switch is named access port, the object returns the access port name. An empty string means invalid value for this object.

hgmpBlacklistRowStatus.name: hgmpBlacklistRowStatus
hgmpBlacklistRowStatus.description: The row status of this table.

hgmpMemberPriPortTable.name: hgmpMemberPriPortTable
hgmpMemberPriPortTable.description: This table contains port number for different network protocols on each member switch. The port number can be used to access a specified member switch with specified protocol and private IP address.

hgmpMemberPriPortEntry.name: hgmpMemberPriPortEntry
hgmpMemberPriPortEntry.description: Information about a specified member private port entry. The indexes of the entry are hgmpGrpMemberDevId and hgmpMemberPriPortProto, which indicate entries in the table.

hgmpMemberDevId.name: hgmpMemberDevId
hgmpMemberDevId.description: Unique identifier indicating the switch in cluster. Value format of the this object is 'XXXXYYYYYY', in which 'XXXX' is is reserved as 4 bytes of 0x0, 'YYYYYY' is a MAC address.

hgmpMemberPriPortProto.name: hgmpMemberPriPortProto
hgmpMemberPriPortProto.description: The index of this table. Each instance value of this object corresponds to a different protocol.

hgmpMemberPriPortProtoDescr.name: hgmpMemberPriPortProtoDescr
hgmpMemberPriPortProtoDescr.description: It describes the hgmpMemberPriPortProtocol object value. For example, it is 'SNMP' when hgmpMemberPriPortProtocol value is 1.

hgmpMemberPriPortNum.name: hgmpMemberPriPortNum
hgmpMemberPriPortNum.description: The private port number of member switch, used by specified hgmpMemberPriPortProto. By using the private IP address, specified protocol and port number, other devices outside cluster can access member switch. The private IP address can be acquired by reading hgmpGrpMemberIpAddr.

hwStackObject.name: hwStackObject
hwStackObject.description: This MIB contains objects to manage the stack operations, which is used on lanswitch products.

hgmpStackMemberTableChange.name: hgmpStackMemberTableChange
hgmpStackMemberTableChange.description: Change identifier of the stack member table.

hgmpStackMemberDisconRate.name: hgmpStackMemberDisconRate
hgmpStackMemberDisconRate.description: Disconnection rate of the stack member switches.

hgmpMainLanswitchFlag.name: hgmpMainLanswitchFlag
hgmpMainLanswitchFlag.description: The status of the local switch in the stack.

hgmpStackIpPoolStartIP.name: hgmpStackIpPoolStartIP
hgmpStackIpPoolStartIP.description: The first address of the management IP network segment assigned by the master switch, which cannot be modified in the case that there is IP address assignment.

hgmpStackIpPoolLength.name: hgmpStackIpPoolLength
hgmpStackIpPoolLength.description: The length of the management IP segment assigned by the master switch, which cannot be modified in the case that there is IP address assignment.

hgmpStackIpPoolMask.name: hgmpStackIpPoolMask
hgmpStackIpPoolMask.description: The mask of the management IP segment assigned by the master switch, which cannot be modified in the case that there is IP address assignment.

hgmpStackMemberDeviceId.name: hgmpStackMemberDeviceId
hgmpStackMemberDeviceId.description: 2 bytes address type of the switch + 2 bytes zero + MAC address, expressed as a hexadecimal number string.

hgmpStackMemberSerial.name: hgmpStackMemberSerial
hgmpStackMemberSerial.description: When adding a member switch to the stack, the master switch will assign an unique integer to identify it.

hgmpStackMemberIpAddr.name: hgmpStackMemberIpAddr
hgmpStackMemberIpAddr.description: The private member IP address for the communication inside the stack.

hgmpStackMemberPassword.name: hgmpStackMemberPassword
hgmpStackMemberPassword.description: Member password for joining a stack.

hgmpStackMemberPlatform.name: hgmpStackMemberPlatform
hgmpStackMemberPlatform.description: Set the hardware platform. A null string indicates the information does not exist in the device adjacency table.

hgmpStackMemberStatus.name: hgmpStackMemberStatus
hgmpStackMemberStatus.description: Member status on the master switch, use for displaying the network management status.

hgmpStackMemberDisconCount.name: hgmpStackMemberDisconCount
hgmpStackMemberDisconCount.description: Count of inside communication disconnection between the member switch and the master switch.

hgmpStackMemberEnrollTime.name: hgmpStackMemberEnrollTime
hgmpStackMemberEnrollTime.description: Enrollment time of the member, measured in seconds.

hgmpStackRole.name: hgmpStackRole
hgmpStackRole.description: This switch's role status in stack.

hgmpStackMaxPoolNum.name: hgmpStackMaxPoolNum
hgmpStackMaxPoolNum.description: Max switch members in one stack that the switch support (include main switch).

hgmpStackMainSwMac.name: hgmpStackMainSwMac
hgmpStackMainSwMac.description: The MAC address of main switch. It will be 00.00.00 when not be a member of stack.

hwNDPObject.name: hwNDPObject
hwNDPObject.description: This MIB contains objects to manage the ndp operations, which are used on lanswitch products.

hwNDPHelloTimer.name: hwNDPHelloTimer
hwNDPHelloTimer.description: NDP packet transmission interval, measured in seconds.

hwNDPAgingTime.name: hwNDPAgingTime
hwNDPAgingTime.description: How long the NDP information of the local switch can be hold in the adjacent switch, measured in seconds.

hwNDPChange.name: hwNDPChange
hwNDPChange.description: Change identifier of the Neighbor table

hwNDPPortTable.name: hwNDPPortTable
hwNDPPortTable.description: Configure to enable/disable the interface NDP of the switch.

hwNDPIfIndex.name: hwNDPIfIndex
hwNDPIfIndex.description: Unique identifier of an interface of the device.

hwNDPPortStatus.name: hwNDPPortStatus
hwNDPPortStatus.description: If it is enable, the device will send and receive the NDP packets via the interface. To disable the NDP function on the interface, set the entry as false.

hwNDPPortNbTable.name: hwNDPPortNbTable
hwNDPPortNbTable.description: NDP neighbor information on the switch.

hwNDPPortNbDeviceId.name: hwNDPPortNbDeviceId
hwNDPPortNbDeviceId.description: 2 bytes address type of the member switch + 2 bytes zero + MAC address, expressed as a character string of the hexadecimal number.

hwNDPPortNbPortName.name: hwNDPPortNbPortName
hwNDPPortNbPortName.description: Unique identifier of a port. A null string indicates that the field was not included in in the latest NDP packet. Interface type + card number / slot number / sequence number.

hwNDPPortNbDeviceName.name: hwNDPPortNbDeviceName
hwNDPPortNbDeviceName.description: Device name. A null string indicates that the field was not included in the latest NDP packet.

hwNDPPortNbProductVer.name: hwNDPPortNbProductVer
hwNDPPortNbProductVer.description: Product version. A null string indicates that the field was not included in the latest NDP packet.

hwNDPPortNbHardVer.name: hwNDPPortNbHardVer
hwNDPPortNbHardVer.description: Hardware version. A null string indicates that the field was not included in the latest NDP packet.

hwNDPPortNbBootromVer.name: hwNDPPortNbBootromVer
hwNDPPortNbBootromVer.description: Bootrom version. A null string indicates that the field was not included in the latest NDP packet.

hwNDPPortNbSoftVer.name: hwNDPPortNbSoftVer
hwNDPPortNbSoftVer.description: Software version. A null string indicates that the field was not included in the latest NDP packet.

hwNDPPortNbAgingtime.name: hwNDPPortNbAgingtime
hwNDPPortNbAgingtime.description: How long the NDP information of the local switch can be hold in the adjacent switch, measured in seconds.

hwNTDPObject.name: hwNTDPObject
hwNTDPObject.description: This MIB contains objects to manage the ntdp operations, which are used on lanswitch products.

hgmpNTDPCollectTopTime.name: hgmpNTDPCollectTopTime
hgmpNTDPCollectTopTime.description: Topology collection interval of the administrator switch of the cluster, measured in minutes.

hgmpNTDPHopRange.name: hgmpNTDPHopRange
hgmpNTDPHopRange.description: Range of the topology collection of the administrator switch

hgmpNTDPRun.name: hgmpNTDPRun
hgmpNTDPRun.description: Enable/Disable the NTDP function on the switch.

hgmpNTDPPortDelay.name: hgmpNTDPPortDelay
hgmpNTDPPortDelay.description: Set the delay to forward the topology request via the ports, measured in milliseconds.

hgmpNTDPHopDelay.name: hgmpNTDPHopDelay
hgmpNTDPHopDelay.description: Set the delay to forward the topology request from every hop, measured in milliseconds.

hgmpNTDPLastTopCollectDuration.name: hgmpNTDPLastTopCollectDuration
hgmpNTDPLastTopCollectDuration.description: Duration of the latest overall topology collection, a performance count measured in seconds.

hgmpNTDPCacheChange.name: hgmpNTDPCacheChange
hgmpNTDPCacheChange.description: Add 1 when the device table changes. The network administrator will check if it has changed before accessing the table. If it has not changed, he will not access again.

hgmpNTDPTOPTableChange.name: hgmpNTDPTOPTableChange
hgmpNTDPTOPTableChange.description: Add 1 when the topology table changes. The network administrator will check if it has changed before accessing the table. If it has not changed, he will not access again.

hgmpNTDPInterfaceTable.name: hgmpNTDPInterfaceTable
hgmpNTDPInterfaceTable.description: Enable/Disable the NTDP on the switch port.

hgmpNTDPInterfaceIfIndex.name: hgmpNTDPInterfaceIfIndex
hgmpNTDPInterfaceIfIndex.description: Unique identifier an interface of the device.

hgmpNTDPInterfaceEnable.name: hgmpNTDPInterfaceEnable
hgmpNTDPInterfaceEnable.description: If it is true, the device will send and receive the NTDP packets via the interface. To disable the NTDP function on the interface, set the entry as false.

hgmpNTDPCacheTable.name: hgmpNTDPCacheTable
hgmpNTDPCacheTable.description: Access the information about the switch from the topology table.

hgmpNTDPCacheHashIndex.name: hgmpNTDPCacheHashIndex
hgmpNTDPCacheHashIndex.description: Our NTDP information is saved in the HASH table on the administrator switch. Using DeviceID as index will lead to the comparison of a large amount of character strings, which puts too many burdens on the administrator switch. A HAHSIndex is added to reduce the character string comparison to the least range.

hgmpNTDPCacheDeviceID.name: hgmpNTDPCacheDeviceID
hgmpNTDPCacheDeviceID.description: 2 bytes address type of the member switch + 2 bytes zero + MAC address, expressed as a character string of the hexadecimal number.

hgmpNTDPCacheClusterName.name: hgmpNTDPCacheClusterName
hgmpNTDPCacheClusterName.description: Name of the cluster including the device.

hgmpNTDPCacheClusterRole.name: hgmpNTDPCacheClusterRole
hgmpNTDPCacheClusterRole.description: Cluster role of the current device, which can be a administrator switch (0x01), member switch(0x02), backup switch(0x03), candidate switch(0x10) or an independent switch (incapable of cluster member) (0x11).

hgmpNTDPCacheCapabilities.name: hgmpNTDPCacheCapabilities
hgmpNTDPCacheCapabilities.description: The capabilities of the device. FF indicates that the field was not included in in the latest NTDP packet.

hgmpNTDPCacheVersion.name: hgmpNTDPCacheVersion
hgmpNTDPCacheVersion.description: The version information of the corresponding device. A null string indicates that the field was not included in in the latest NTDP packet.

hgmpNTDPCachePlatform.name: hgmpNTDPCachePlatform
hgmpNTDPCachePlatform.description: Hardware platform. A null string indicates that the field was not included in the latest NTDP packet.

hgmpNTDPCacheMngVLAN.name: hgmpNTDPCacheMngVLAN
hgmpNTDPCacheMngVLAN.description: The management VLAN ID of the device.

hgmpNTDPTopTable.name: hgmpNTDPTopTable
hgmpNTDPTopTable.description: Access the topology structure collected by the NTDP.

hgmpNTDPTopHashIndex.name: hgmpNTDPTopHashIndex
hgmpNTDPTopHashIndex.description: Our NTDP information is saved in the HASH table on the administrator switch. Using DeviceID as index will lead to the comparison of a large amount of character strings, which puts too many burdens on the administrator switch. A HAHSIndex is added to reduce the character string comparison to the least range.

hgmpNTDPTopEdgeStartDevID.name: hgmpNTDPTopEdgeStartDevID
hgmpNTDPTopEdgeStartDevID.description: 2 bytes address type of the member switch + 2 bytes zero + MAC address, expressed as a character string of the hexadecimal number.

hgmpNTDPTopEdgeIndex.name: hgmpNTDPTopEdgeIndex
hgmpNTDPTopEdgeIndex.description: Edge index of this entry in the data structure.

hgmpNTDPTopEdgeEndDevID.name: hgmpNTDPTopEdgeEndDevID
hgmpNTDPTopEdgeEndDevID.description: 2 bytes address type of the member switch + 2 bytes zero + MAC address, expressed as a character string of the hexadecimal number.

hgmpNTDPTopEdgeStartPort.name: hgmpNTDPTopEdgeStartPort
hgmpNTDPTopEdgeStartPort.description: The number of the first port of a topology edge. Interface type + card number / slot number / sequence number.

hgmpNTDPTopEdgeStartPortFullDuplex.name: hgmpNTDPTopEdgeStartPortFullDuplex
hgmpNTDPTopEdgeStartPortFullDuplex.description: The full-duplex status of the first port on a topology edge.

hgmpNTDPTopEdgeStartPortSpeed.name: hgmpNTDPTopEdgeStartPortSpeed
hgmpNTDPTopEdgeStartPortSpeed.description: The speed of the first port on a topology edge.

hgmpNTDPTopEdgeEndPort.name: hgmpNTDPTopEdgeEndPort
hgmpNTDPTopEdgeEndPort.description: The number of the last port of a topology edge. Interface type + card number / slot number / sequence number.

hgmpNTDPTopLinkStatus.name: hgmpNTDPTopLinkStatus
hgmpNTDPTopLinkStatus.description: In STP or RSTP, it describes link status according to port STP steady status. In MSTP it describes STP steady status of the instance which management VLAN belongs to. Either 'hgmpNTDPTopEdgeStartPort' or 'hgmpNTDPTopEdgeEndPort' STP steady status is 'blocking', this object is 'blocking', otherwise is 'forwarding'. If STP or MSTP is disabled, this object is 'forwarding'.

hgmpStackMemberfailure.name: hgmpStackMemberfailure
hgmpStackMemberfailure.description: When a stack member failure, send a snmp trap to the network management.

hgmpStackMemberRecover.name: hgmpStackMemberRecover
hgmpStackMemberRecover.description: When a stack member Recover, send a snmp trap to the network management.

hgmpStackMemberStatusChange.name: hgmpStackMemberStatusChange
hgmpStackMemberStatusChange.description: When a stack member status change, send a snmp trap to the network management.
